# RBAC & Security

## Roles

| Role | ID examples | Notes |
|------|-------------|-------|
| `cs` | rina, budi, sari | Assigned + unassigned + active manual shares |
| `supervisor` | admin | Team-wide access via `ROLE_PERMISSIONS` |
| `owner` | hartono | Supervisor permissions + billing, export approval, field rules |

**Owner is not CS.** Never gate team features with `role === "supervisor"` alone — use `role !== "cs"` or `hasPermission`.

## Required helpers

```tsx
hasPermission(role, "manage_agents")
canAccessCustomer(agent, customer)   // list/filter visibility
canEditCustomer(agent, customer)     // enforce on edit forms
shareBadgeFor(agent, customer)       // "Dibagikan" badge
getFieldDisplay(field, value, role, fieldRules)
maskPhone(phone, role)
canViewAuditEntry(viewerRole, entryActorRole, action)
```

## Manual shares

- Stored on `customer.manualShares[]`; respect `expiresAt`.
- Create/revoke via store → auto `logAudit`.
- Share modal: agent picker (CS only), permission view/edit, reason, duration.

## Audit log

Call `logAudit` for: login, reassign, role change, export request/approve/deny, manual share, phone viewed full (supervisor+), field rule changes, agent CRUD.

Action types must exist in `AuditAction` union (`src/types/index.ts`).

## Settings gating

Mirror `settings.tsx`: each section has `requires: Permission`. Use `<Gated perm="...">` pattern for new owner/supervisor sections.

## Export workflow

- Supervisor: `createExportRequest` → pending
- Owner: `exportDataDirect` or `approveExportRequest` / `denyExportRequest`

## Common bugs to prevent

- Owner sees CS dashboard (missing team charts)
- CS sees other agents' assigned customers without share
- Raw phone in DOM for CS role
- Audit entries visible to supervisor that should be owner-only
